  <label for="email" class="block text-sm font-bold text-brand-dark mb-1">Email</label>
  <input type="email" name="email" id="email" class="block w-full px-4 py-3 rounded-lg border border-brand-grey-light focus:ring-brand-red focus:border-brand-red shadow-sm sm:text-sm placeholder-brand-grey-medium" placeholder="you@example.com">
</div>
Input Field (Dark):
HTML

<div>
  <label for="email_dark" class="block text-sm font-bold text-brand-white mb-1">Email</label>
  <input type="email" name="email_dark" id="email_dark" class="block w-full px-4 py-3 rounded-lg border border-brand-grey-dark bg-brand-near-dark text-brand-white focus:ring-brand-red focus:border-brand-red shadow-sm sm:text-sm placeholder-brand-grey-medium" placeholder="you@example.com">
</div>
Checkbox/Radio (with red accent):
Requires custom styling or a Tailwind plugin like @tailwindcss/forms which you can then customize.
Focus on making the checked state use brand-red.
Example with @tailwindcss/forms (conceptual): class="form-checkbox rounded text-brand-red focus:ring-brand-red"
